    { title:'1920s — De Stijl & Bauhaus',
      body:'Piet Mondrian and Theo van Doesburg founded De Stijl in the Netherlands, restricting painting to horizontal/vertical lines and primary colors — seeking universal visual harmony. The Bauhaus in Weimar unified fine art and industrial design, teaching geometry as the foundation of beauty. Both movements believed abstraction could transform everyday life.',
