      body:'Max Bill and the Abstraction-Creation group formulated Concrete Art: work created purely from visual elements with no metaphorical content. Unlike abstract art derived from nature, Concrete Art was entirely invented and constructed through mathematical precision. The Circle and Square manifesto demanded purity of visual means, influencing Swiss graphic design for decades.',
      works:'Max Bill: Fifteen Variations on a Single Theme (1935). Sophie Taeuber-Arp: Composition (1931).',
      draw:function(cv,cx){ cx.fillStyle='#fff'; cx.fillRect(0,0,200,155); var cols=['#7c3aed','#f59e0b','#ef4444','#3b82f6','#22c55e']; for(var i=0;i<5;i++){ cx.strokeStyle=cols[i]; cx.lineWidth=2.5; cx.beginPath(); cx.arc(100,77,18+i*14,0,Math.PI*2); cx.stroke(); cx.strokeStyle=cols[4-i]; cx.lineWidth=1; var s=25+i*22; cx.strokeRect(100-s/2,77-s*0.35,s,s*0.7); } }
    },
    { title:'1940s — Abstract Expressionism',
      body:'Post-WWII New York became the center of abstract expressionism. Jackson Pollock dripped paint emphasizing process over product. Mark Rothko painted hovering luminous rectangles evoking vast emotional states. Willem de Kooning fused gestural mark-making with raw energy. The movement declared the act of painting itself as the primary meaning.',
      works:'Pollock: No. 31 (1950). Rothko: Ochre and Red on Red (1954). de Kooning: Woman I (1952).',
      draw:function(cv,cx){ cx.fillStyle='#111'; cx.fillRect(0,0,200,155); for(var i=0;i<180;i++){ cx.strokeStyle=['#f59e0b','#ef4444','#a78bfa','#fff','#3b82f6'][Math.floor(Math.random()*5)]; cx.lineWidth=Math.random()*2+0.4; cx.globalAlpha=0.6+Math.random()*0.4; cx.beginPath(); var sx=Math.random()*200,sy=Math.random()*155; cx.moveTo(sx,sy); cx.quadraticCurveTo(sx+Math.random()*60-30,sy+Math.random()*60-30,sx+Math.random()*80-40,sy+Math.random()*80-40); cx.stroke(); } cx.globalAlpha=1; }
